Thursday, March 13th 2014

This week we introduce readers to our new crony capitalism index.
"Rent-seeking" is how economists describe making money out of
political connections. Some sectors of the economy, such as oil,
gas, mining and banking, are more susceptible to it than others.
Our index calculates the proportion of billionaire wealth made in
those sectors, and indexes it across countries and over time, to
indicate how crony capitalists are doing around the world

